TY  - JOUR
TI  - Quadrature-Based Methods for Obtaining Approximate Solutions to Nonlinear Asset Pricing Models
AU  - Tauchen, George
AU  - Hussey, Robert
AB  - [The paper develops a discrete state space solution method for a class of nonlinear rational expectations models. The method works by using numerical quadrature rules to approximate the integral operators that arise in stochastic intertemporal models. The method is particularly useful for approximating asset pricing models and has potential applications in other problems as well. An empirical application uses the method to study the relationship between the risk premium and the conditional variability of the equity return under an ARCH endowment process.]
